article.headline: Penn 78, Campbell 67
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. -- Jack Eggleston led five Penn scorers in double figures with 16 points as the Quakers defeated Campbell 78-67 in the consolation game of the UCF Holiday Classic on Tuesday night. Lewis Cameron added 14 points and seven rebounds, Tyler Bernardini finished with 13 points, Votel Brennan added 11 and Zack Rosen chipped in 10 for the Quakers. Jonathan Rodriguez scored 18 points and pulled down nine rebounds for Campbell, which lost for the seventh time in its last eight games. Miles Taylor added 17 points and seven rebounds. Penn led 36-29 at halftime on the strength of Eggleston's 11 points, as the Quakers shot 55 percent from the floor in the first half. The Quakers (2-7) led by as many as 26 points in the second half. Campbell (3-8) outrebounded Penn 38-29 in the game, but shot only 38 percent from the floor.
